                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 3, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White reports that he has just had an interview with the British minister
                    for foreign affairs, who inquired whether Mr. White thought <gap quantity="1"
                        unit="words"/> Government of the United States would object to Mr. Bowen’s
                    designation to effect immediate settlement. Mr. White replied in the negative,
                    stating that he felt sure if such had been the case he would have been
                    instructed to that effect. Mr. White’s reply appeared to afford satisfaction to
                    Lord Lansdowne, who hopes to be able at an early date to make a formal answer to
                    Mr. White’s communication of January 1.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
